# Authorised release-attestation signers for flock (OpenSSH allowed_signers format).
#
# `git verify-tag` / `ssh-keygen -Y verify` checks a signed release tag against
# this file. The principal is the project's release identity, NOT any individual —
# the matching private half lives only in the maintainer's out-of-band backup
# (native/release-signing-key, gitignored), like the APK keystore.
#
# Rotating the key = append the new line here (keep the old so historical tags
# still verify) and record the change in a signed commit. Never delete a line a
# past tag was signed with.
#
# Verify a release tag:
#   git config gpg.ssh.allowedSignersFile docs/transparency/allowed_signers
#   git verify-tag release/<build>
#
# The key signs in two namespaces: "git" (release tags) and
# "flock-pwa-manifest" (the PWA asset manifest, scripts/sign-pwa-manifest.mjs).
# Distinct namespaces mean one signature can never be replayed as the other.
#
# principal                              options            key
releases@flock.forgesworn.dev namespaces="git,flock-pwa-manifest" ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAII5D3Fwt4jTxxrdbyXIP1DE/iiS9teXADyDQC6CbB1sS
